            "creation_date": 1393826087,
            "body": "<p>On the first thread you linked to, the regex you put below the link is nowhere to be found on the page. Were you really using a regex from that page? The regex that was suggested was:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>(\\w+|)?\\$?(?:\\bXF[A-D]|X[A-E][A-Z]|[A-W][A-Z]{2}|[A-Z]{2}|[A-Z])\\$?(?:104857[0-6]|10485[0-6]\\d|1048[0-4]\\d{2}|104[0-7]\\d{3}|10[0-3]\\d{4}|[1-9]\\d{1,5}|[1-9])d?\\b(:\\s?\\$?(?:\\bXF[A-D]|X[A-E][A-Z]|[A-W][A-Z]{2}|[A-Z]{2}|[A-Z])\\$?(?:104857[0-6]|10485[0-6]\\d|1048[0-4]\\d{2}|104[0-7]\\d{3}|10[0-3]\\d{4}|[1-9]\\d{1,5}|[1-9])d?\\b)?\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Try that.<\/p>\n\n<p>Also, it would help to know what <em>specific<\/em> strings don't get matched correctly, since you mentioned that some of them work.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 22139623,
